c. Safeguard Protection Analysis

RI-363, "Process Hazards Analysis and Layers of Protection Analysis," satisfies the requirements of Section 2762.2.1 of the CalARP regulation.



The Layers of Protection Analysis (LOPA) program was initiated in 2014 to assess the effectiveness of existing PHA safeguards and recommended safeguards to reduce the probability and/or severity of a catastrophic release.



Layers of Protection Analysis is a risk assessment tool that uses a semi-quantitative method to evaluate qualifying process unit hazard scenarios to determine if sufficient Independent Protection Layers (IPLs) are available to protect against process safety accidents and to protect personnel, the general public and the environment.



An Independent Protection Layer is an approved and validated safeguard available to prevent initiation of a hazard scenario or escalation of its consequence. IPLs may be passive or active and preventative or mitigating, and may include containment areas, critical alarms, Safety Instrumented Functions (SIFs), Pressure Rel

