The Employee Participation Plan ensures that:

- Refinery workers are consulted on, and can participate in, PHAs, DMRs, LOPAs, Major Incident Investigations, HCAs, and MOCs. Other employees with responsibilities relating to specific processes are consulted prior to and during the elements listed above. Worker involvement is documented in reports.  

- Operations and Maintenance workers and their representatives are consulted on the development of all prevention program elements and the Emergency Response Program. Examples of participation include the following:

(a) Development and review of procedures, with participation documented in the Electronic Manuals and Management System (EMMS);

(b) Development and revision of Refinery Instructions;

(c) Integral members of Incident Investigation teams, with participation documented in the incident report;

(d) Consultation on appropriate type and frequency of training;

(e) Involvement in various safety activities such as Joint Health & Safety Meetings, PSM Steering Committee and Human Factors Team, with participation documented in the meeting minutes

(f) Participation in MOC activities such as Health & Safety Evaluations, training and PSSRs, which are documented in the MOC database

